{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8d81988e-036e-47c9-9c5a-30ea626dbbc4","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated  += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Action | Events fired |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | `Created` → `Activated` |\n| User switches away | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` |\n| User returns | `Resumed` → `Activated` |\n| App closed | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` → `Destroying` |\n\n> `Backgrounding` is iOS/Mac Catalyst only — use it to save state before the OS may terminate your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"32bebf9e-a26d-4fb3-81f9-21bb8cc7b2c2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":410,"requestId":"7FCD:7D36C:60D6103:69A4D0C:69F156B1"},"id":"cbfb3798-1873-4ba1-8db3-8e4735f32820","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:54:18.449Z","parentId":"ffaf172f-9a5e-4387-acb8-a87a745171ee"}
